(9252, 651, '_elementor_data', '[{\"id\":\"4c75efb8\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"hover_parallax\":[{\"layer_position_vr\":{\"unit\":\"%\",\"size\":30},\"layer_position_hr\":{\"unit\":\"%\",\"size\":40},\"_id\":\"86532b0\"},{\"layer_position_vr\":{\"unit\":\"%\",\"size\":60},\"layer_position_hr\":{\"unit\":\"%\",\"size\":20},\"_id\":\"e627e0c\"}]},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"4d0c6779\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"7e7117bb\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>This year, India is celebrating its 78th Independence Day on August 15. This day is celebrated with great vigour and zeal all over the country. On this day, we remember the freedom fighters who fought for our nation\'s independence. People also organise cultural programs and seminars to pay tribute to the freedom fighters who sacrificed their lives for India\'s freedom. But did you know that on this day, the Indian flag is hoisted, not furled? The terms \\\"flag hoisting\\\" and \\\"flag unfurling\\\" are commonly interchanged, but they represent different techniques for presenting the national flag.<\\/p><p>So, here\'s a look at the subtle yet significant difference in how the national flag is presented on Independence Day and Republic Day in India.<\\/p>\",\"text_color\":\"#646464\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Noto Sans\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":15,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_font_weight\":\"400\",\"typography_line_height\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":25,\"sizes\":[]}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"20383cc\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"hover_parallax\":[{\"layer_position_vr\":{\"unit\":\"%\",\"size\":30},\"layer_position_hr\":{\"unit\":\"%\",\"size\":40},\"_id\":\"86532b0\"},{\"layer_position_vr\":{\"unit\":\"%\",\"size\":60},\"layer_position_hr\":{\"unit\":\"%\",\"size\":20},\"_id\":\"e627e0c\"}]},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"593919b\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"af7bbcd\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"title\":\"Difference between unfurling and hoisting the flag?\",\"title_color\":\"#000000\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Noto Sans\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":25,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_font_weight\":\"600\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"},{\"id\":\"625c57c\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"The crucial difference lies in how the tricolour is positioned during the two ceremonies. On Independence Day, the flag is positioned at the bottom of the pole and is raised (hoisted) by the Prime Minister, from the bottom to the top.\\n\\nOn Republic Day, the flag is folded or rolled up and attached to the top of the pole. It is then unveiled (unfurled) by the President, who does so without pulling it up.\",\"text_color\":\"#646464\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Noto Sans\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":15,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_font_weight\":\"400\",\"typography_line_height\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":25,\"sizes\":[]}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"3487ae4\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"hover_parallax\":[{\"layer_position_vr\":{\"unit\":\"%\",\"size\":30},\"layer_position_hr\":{\"unit\":\"%\",\"size\":40},\"_id\":\"86532b0\"},{\"layer_position_vr\":{\"unit\":\"%\",\"size\":60},\"layer_position_hr\":{\"unit\":\"%\",\"size\":20},\"_id\":\"e627e0c\"}],\"padding\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"25\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"e4d1a94\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"6dfd9ff\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"title\":\"Why the flag is hoisted and not unfurled on Independence Day?\",\"title_color\":\"#000000\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Noto Sans\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":25,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_font_weight\":\"600\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"},{\"id\":\"9764e96\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>On Independence Day, the Prime Minister hoists the flag from the bottom of the pole. Flag hoisting on this day often includes a ceremonial event with a military or civilian honour guard raising the flag while the national anthem is played. The hoisting on Independence Day symbolises the rise of a new nation, patriotism, and freedom from colonial rule.<\\/p>\",\"text_color\":\"#646464\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Noto Sans\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":15,\"sizes\":[]},\"typography_font_weight\":\"400\",\"typography_line_height\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":25,\"sizes\":[]}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
